[normal]Baroness Scotland of Asthal
[normal]: 
[normal]To ask Her Majesty’s Government how the proposed residence test envisaged by the Ministry of Jus
[normal]tice consultation will impact upon the attainment of legal redress by non-
[normal]residents in challenging Government action
[normal].   
[normal]The Minister of State, Ministry of Justice (Lord McNally): 
[normal]Anybody excluded from civil legal aid as a result of the residence test in th
[normal]e future would be entitled to apply for exceptional 
[normal]funding, including in respect of services described in Part 1 of Schedule 1 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 from which the individual has been excluded as a result of the
[normal] residence test. 
